                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-238-off1271 t18270531-238-crimeloc1274"></join> on the 1st of May, about half-past nine o'clock at night, the prisoner came and took this handkerchief out of my basket. I was running at the time, and collared him immediately, he begged of me to let him go.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by Mr. BARRY. Q. Where was this? A. Near a sugar-warehouse - there were some ballan-singers there - I was running past, my handkerchief was picked up - I lost two sixpences from my basket.</p>
               <p>
            
